4-6}}\n* {{cite book |last=Williams |first=Tony |title=Hearths of Darkness: The Family in the American Horror Film |location=Rutherford, New Jersey, United States |publisher=[[Fairleigh Dickinson University Press]] |year=1996 |isbn=978-0-8386-3564-3}}\n{{ref end}}\n\n==External links==\n{{wikiquote|Halloween (1978 film)}}\n* [http://www.halloweenmovies.com Official website of the ''Halloween'' series]\n* {{AFI film}}\n* {{Allrovi movie|21317|Halloween}}\n* {{mojo title}}\n* {{IMDb title|0077651|Halloween}}\n* {{Metacritic film|halloween-1978|Halloween}}\n* {{Rotten Tomatoes|1009113-halloween|Halloween}}\n* {{tcmdb title|77236|Halloween}}\n\n{{Halloween series}}\n{{John Carpenter}}\n{{Authority control}}\n\n[[Category:1970s horror thriller films]]\n[[Category:1970s independent films]]\n[[Category:1970s serial killer films]]\n[[Category:1970s slasher films]]\n[[Category:1978 films]]\n[[Category:1978 horror films]]\n[[Category:American films]]\n[[Category:American horror thriller films]]\n[[Category:American independent films]]\n[[Category:American serial killer films]]\n[[Category:American slasher films]]\n[[Category:American teen films]]\n[[Category:American teen horror films]]\n[[Category:English-language films]]\n[[Category:Films about psychopaths]]\n[[Category:Films directed by John Carpenter]]\n[[Category:Films scored by John Carpenter]]\n[[Category:Films set in 1963]]\n[[Category:Films set in 1978]]\n[[Category:Films set in fictional populated places]]\n[[Category:Films set in Illinois]]\n[[Category:Films set in psychiatric hospitals]]\n[[Category:Films shot in California]]\n[[Category:Films shot in Los Angeles]]\n[[Category:Films adapted into video games]]\n[[Category:Halloween (franchise) films|1]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by Debra Hill]]\n[[Category:Films with screenplays by John Carpenter]]\n[[Category:Sororicide in fiction]]\n[[Category:Teen thriller films]]\n[[Category:United States National Film Registry films]]\n[[Category:American exploitation films]]\n", "name_user": "ZippeyKeys12", "label": "safe", "comment": "Fix duplicate citation of Bob Clark interview", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Halloween_(1978_film)"}
{"title_page": "Boji\u0161t\u011b (Havl\u00ed\u010dk\u016fv Brod District)", "text_new": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name=Boji\u0161t\u011b\n|settlement_type=Municipality\n|image_skyline=K\u0159\u00ed\u017e u Boji\u0161t\u011b.jpg\n|image_shield= Boji\u0161t\u011b CoA.jpg\n|image_flag=Boji\u0161t\u011b HB flag.jpg\n|subdivision_type=Country\n|subdivision_name={{CZE}}\n|subdivision_type1=[[Regions of the Czech Republic|Region]]\n|subdivision_name1=[[Vyso\u010dina Region|Vyso\u010dina]]\n|subdivision_type2=[[Districts of the Czech Republic|District]]\n|subdivision_name2=[[Havl\u00ed\u010dk\u016fv Brod District|Havl\u00ed\u010dk\u016fv Brod]]\n|coordinates = {{coord|49|40|3|N|15|16|43|E|region:CZ|display=inline,title}}\n|pushpin_map=Czech Republic|area_total_km2= 7.27\n|population_total= 266\n|population_as_of= 1.1.2014\n|population_density_km2= auto\n|elevation_m= 474\n|postal_code_type=Postal&nbsp;code|postal_code=584&nbsp;01\n}}\n\n'''Boji\u0161t\u011b''' ({{IPA-cs|\u02c8boj\u026a\u0283c\u025b}}) is a village and municipality (''[[obec]]'') in [[Havl\u00ed\u010dk\u016fv Brod District]] in the [[Vyso\u010dina Region]] of the Czech Republic.\n\nThe municipality covers an area of {{convert|7.27|km2|sqmi}}, and has a population of 256 (as at 28&nbsp;August 2006).\n\nBoji\u0161t\u011b lies approximately {{convert|23|km|mi|0}} west of [[Havl\u00ed\u010dk\u016fv Brod]], {{convert|38|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} north-west of [[Jihlava]], and {{convert|78|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} south-east of [[Prague]].\n\n==References==\n*[http://www.czso.cz/lexikon/mos_vdb.nsf/okresy/CZ0631/ Czech Statistical Office: Municipalities of Havl\u00ed\u010dk\u016fv Brod District]{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n{{Havl\u00ed\u010dk\u016fv Brod District}}\n\n\n{{authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bojiste}}\n[[Category:Villages in Havl\u00ed\u010dk\u016fv Brod District]]\n\n\n{{Vyso\u010dina-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox settlement\n|name=Boji\u0161t\u011b\n|settlement_type=Municipality\n|image_skyline=K\u0159\u00ed\u017e u Boji\u0161t\u011b.jpg\n|image_shield= Boji\u0161t\u011b CoA.jpg\n|image_flag=Boji\u0161t\u011b HB flag.jpg\n|subdivision_type=Country\n|subdivision_name={{CZE}}\n|subdivision_type1=[[Regions of the Czech Republic|Region]]\n|subdivision_name1=[[Vyso\u010dina Region|Vyso\u010dina]]\n|subdivision_type2=[[Districts of the Czech Republic|District]]\n|subdivision_name2=[[Havl\u00ed\u010dk\u016fv Brod District|Havl\u00ed\u010dk\u016fv Brod]]\n|coordinates = {{coord|49|40|3|N|15|16|43|E|region:CZ|display=inline,title}}\n|pushpin_map=Czech Republic|area_total_km2= 7.27\n|population_total= 266\n|population_as_of= 1.1.2014\n|population_density_km2= auto\n|elevation_m= 474\n|postal_code_type=Postal&nbsp;code|postal_code=584&nbsp;01\n}}\n\n'''Boji\u0161t\u011b''' ({{IPA-cs|\u02c8boj\u026a\u0283c\u025b}}) is a village and municipality (''[[obec]]'') in [[Havl\u00ed\u010dk\u016fv Brod District]] in the [[Vyso\u010dina Region]] of the Czech Republic.\n\nThe municipality covers an area of {{convert|7.27|km2|sqmi}}, and has a population of 256 (as at 28&nbsp;August 2006).\n\nBoji\u0161t\u011b lies approximately {{convert|23|km|mi|0}} west of [[Havl\u00ed\u010dk\u016fv Brod]], {{convert|38|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} north-west of [[Jihlava]], and {{convert|78|km|mi|0|abbr=on}} south-east of [[Prague]].\n\n==References==\n*[http://www.czso.cz/lexikon/mos_vdb.nsf/okresy/CZ0631/ Czech Statistical Office: Municipalities of Havl\u00ed\u010dk\u016fv Brod District]{{dead link|date=November 2016 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}\n\n{{Havl\u00ed\u010dk\u016fv Brod District}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Bojiste}}\n[[Category:Villages in Havl\u00ed\u010dk\u016fv Brod District]]\n\n\n{{Vyso\u010dina-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Ser Amantio di Nicolao", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200eReferences:add authority control", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Boji%C5%A1t%C4%9B_(Havl%C3%AD%C4%8Dk%C5%AFv_Brod_District)"}
